      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WATTS UP PARTYTIME (11) had to work last start so was far from disgraced when fourth. Will be banking on better luck from another wide barrier but the prior form was strong, finishing fifth to Keayang Zahara in the G1 Hammerhead Mile two back and scoring back-to-back wins prior. CONSTANTINOPLE (10) put the writing on the wall when runner-up two back then powered back into wining form last week, coming from this barrier to score by 7.7m at this circuit and distance. Could go on with it. IMPERIAL MONARCH NZ (9) makes his first visit to Sydney but his Victorian form reads well, winning the Geelong Cup last month and narrowly missing in a Bendigo FFA last start. Manners let I AM HELLBOUND (3) down last start but he had put together a string of wins and placings prior. Draws well so deserves another chance. KYVALLEY MAVEN (4) broke and raced wide so did well to place here last week. Draws to be competitive.",
